				<wikidot:authorName>Laneous</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4894577</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The bulbs guys are the personification of his bad, unused ideas. The reason they attack the book is because, well, they're <em>jealous</em> of that book because it's a better idea than any of them that actually got wrote about.</p> <p>At the same time, I love your interpretation.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12103197#post-4285673</guid>
				<title>+1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12103197/scp-3725#post-4285673</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 19 Jun 2019 18:27:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheBlueHour</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4078000</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Just what the&#8230; what? <em>What?</em></p> <p>So at first I thought the light bulb bois were personifications of the writer's unused ideas, but after reading the ending I started thinking the opposite. That the light bulbs are <em>parasites</em> that steal good writing ideas.</p> <p>Anyway, this is pretty good and you get the right emotions across so +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
